definition.value: An amino pentasaccharide comprising alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and beta-D-glucose residues linked sequentially (2->3), (1->3), (1->4) and (1->4).
An amino disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylmannose that is beta-D-mannopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been converted into the corresponding beta-D-xylopyranosyl derivative.
